{"questionId":"26879","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A Principal would like to compare the students in his school with a national standard.&nbsp;He decides to give a test to eight students made up of four boys and four girls. One of&nbsp;the teachers offers to find the volunteers from his class.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The marks out of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn></math>, for the students who took the test, are:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>29</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>38</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>37</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>27</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>31</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The national standard mark is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math> out of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Two additional students take the test at a later date and the mean mark for all ten students&nbsp;is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and the standard deviation is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>For further analysis, a standardized score out of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn></math> for the ten students is obtained by&nbsp;multiplying the scores by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math> and adding <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For the ten students, find</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the standard deviation of their standardized score.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26879","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ1.3e.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"the standard deviation of their standardized score.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Linear transformation of a single RV, E(X) and VAR(X), unbiased estimators"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}